caption: Went to this nice establishment yesterday to enjoy a nice evening. The establishment was busy and I totally understand. I stood at the bar while the bald bartender blantly ignored me and help the partons around me. I thought the bartender didn't like people of color(still undetermined)but after reading the previous comments, he is naturally unhappy with himself
The food and service were great. We had the fried green tomatoes with pimento cheese. They were amazing. The southern fried chicken is a huge portion and it was delicious.

I would recommend this place. The food could use a tad more seasoning, but it was good. The wings could have been cooked a tad longer. The wings (which were ordered as an appetizer before or meal) came out basically at the same time as or food did which was not ideal as I'm sure you can imagine. I ordered the fried chicken, which was good, the sides were lacking in flavor.  My husband ordered the fish which was excellent as were his sides. The drinks (Moscow mules) were prepared in a timely fashion even though they were busy. The waitress was amazing!!! She was fast, friendly, and knowledgeable!!! We will definitely be back.

Ok...so my wife and I visited here and ordered a few different dishes which were all absolutely delicious! I had the Grouper fillet with asparagus and grits and my wife had fried chicken with mash. They give you some really good portions here and the food is very tasty. We had a server who was nice and despite it being a bit busy she stayed on point with the tables and made sure that we never wanted for anything while there. We definitely enjoyed eating here and will definitely return. Thank you for a great experience!
Casual feeling upper-story bar and restaurant boasting solid bar food. Low key until late in the evening when it turns into more of a bar than a restaurant. Drinks are average in quality.
Service from Daryl was amazing. Loved the food. Thanks for a great time!!!!
Great service! Tippy is the BEST!
Amazing!

I love an open air/roof top bar. You can’t go wrong with an evening of people watching and drinking. We visited after dinner so we came to try the drinks. My husband enjoyed whatever he drank but I asked the bartender for a recommendation (I know rookie mistake) and I said I was looking for something sweet with rum. I thought I was going to get a mixed drink. She brings out something called a bushwacker. It was like drinking a dessert...it was so sweet that after a few sips I had to sit it to the side. I’m sure someone else would love that but it wasn’t my thing. So just make sure to be as specific as possible if you don’t know what you want to drink and ask what is in whatever they recommend lol. The pictures of the food look great so I look forward to visiting again, possibly for brunch and not another bushwacker.
Great food and atmosphere

This place has a great balance between a perky, hopping bar, and a cozy restaurant. It's not too loud unlike so many bars, no sports blasting. You can stand and mill around chatting, or find a quieter corner to sit. The food is decent, bit pricey for the quality. A $16 sandwich? They've got good happy hour deals though. And they have pretty good drink offerings. The best French 75 I've ever been served. The staff is also super nice. My sister has a ton of allergies and the chef couldn't figure out how to make it safe for her at first, but they were willing to make it over, no problems.
Great atmosphere! Friendly staff. Bartenders were on their game!! 200+ shots poured in 30 minutes!!  Highly recommend!!
Great staff and a cool place to hang out!!

Love the staff, love the drinks, but the CHIPS AND DIP!?!? They put your first chip into the dip so once it arrives you will have one soggy, handpicked chip. I would give 5 stars, but the chip thing man... stop that. SMH
Great spot for Sunday brunch and catching the game.
The best goat cheese balls and fried green tomatoes!

Cool venue on the second floor overlooking the street. It has lots of TVs to catch a game, cool atmosphere, and lots of potential.  However, just because it's on the second floor doesn't mean you should charge $28 for a 2 oz pour of Blanton's and $22 for 2 oz pour of Angels Envy.  If you go, stick with beer and skip the food.  If you want a good cocktail at a decent price, go to SIP, the bottle, or cotton row.
Great Spicy options for wings and chicken sandwiches.
Ordered a bloody mary, bartender used bare hands when putting food in them. Owner proceeded to kick us out when bringing the issue to light.
Great food, drinks, service
Great drinks good food.  Fried Chicken and Nashville Hot Chicken Sandwhich were both very good.
Cool place. Great staff!
Delicious meal and exemplary service.  Will definitely return.
Quiet atmosphere  - good food - and excellent beverage selection.  Tippy is "the Man"!
Great place"
Great place to relax and enjoy a drink.  Great atmosphere and venue.   We did not order food, typical bar food menu it appeared to be good.   Others around me ordered and what I saw looked good.
Mar is a great place  to  eat  and  hangout  with  family and friends
Best indoor/outdoor space downtown, service & food are both pleasantly surprisingly.
The food and atmosphere are always great at The Martin!

Today me and a couple of friends sat and ate here. The service was incredible, even handled by one bartender himself! He was super sweet, nice and even with his hands full managed to get out me and my friends drinks, food and snapped a couple of awesome pics for us as we wined and dined ourselves! 10/10 would recommend this place! The view upstairs was amazing and the food was fast, fresh and delicious. You guys damn sure will have my service again here soon! Much love❤️
Great food and service!
Great beers great food
Good bar with good food.
Good scenery
I've only been for brunch, but both visits were wonderful. The Chicken and Waffles is fantastic, and so was the Eggs Florentine. The great open air view and friendly staff make the experience
Absolutely amazing service food was unreal
Great atmosphere upstairs inside what used to be Huntsville's premier movie theater. Awesome place to meet friends but fabulous food too. Try the fried goat cheese. Yum!
Great food. Super awesome server!  All around fun spot.
Great food, atmosphere and service. Can't believe I just found this place. New favorite spot downtown.

It's upstairs. Not too many though. Bright open space. Roll up garage doors allow for open air view of street. Only been for brunch so far. They nail great Hollandaise on Eggs Florentine. Tried goat cheese balls w a yummy honey dipping sauce. The bed of baby spinach and grape tomatoes  was fresh and good w it all. Shrimp and grits were great as was the sausage gravy biscuits. Mimosa special till noon made everything just fantastic. We'll be back!
Great lunch spot downtown!
service was average. fair menu. limited beer selection on draft. kinda goofy crowd w ok atmosphere. Not bad just been to better. Prob better in the summer when they open the garage doors
Fried green tomatoes are the best ever!!!! Excellent service.

The slim bearded bartender guy was very dry and not friendly at all! He brought our food and didn’t check on us until we flagged him down and it took several attempts to get his attention. All of the bartenders were too busy on their phones to pay attention to us.
Cool hangout downtown.  Great beers and good wings
Love this place. Great food and Awesome service
Shrimp tacos with the street corn are AMAZING!
Nice bar good food
Decent place to have drinks.
Great food and drinks!

Great relaxing atmosphere with frozen drinks at a great price. I was surprised to know they offer Sushi Salmon and my wife greatly enjoyed.  They even had a fantasy football draft in addition to the different choices of craft beer and recipes.  Thanks for having us out on Sunday, we will be back.
Some of the best bar food around with a comfy and open atmosphere. I highly recommend the cheese curds.

A great open air bar located right above Sammy T's Music Hall! The island bar is large and with the garage doors opened the air flow is perfect. Appetizers and Entrees here were both delicious and promptly delivered. When it came to ordering drinks from the bar, Saira was very attentive and was very knowledgeable when it came to trying different drinks. My favorite day to come is Thursday when it's 1/2 off wings and $2 Yuengling on draft!
Great atmosphere.
I like the layout however one of the male bartenders has horrible customer service.
Cool atmosphere. Flatbreads were great. Friendly, courteous server.
Sunday brunch was delicious! Best fried green tomatoes were the best.
Cool environment and good staff.  Good was decent but nothing extraordinary
Great food & drinks!! Always a good time at The Martin!
Great bartenders and food!

This is the best bar food in Huntsville Alabama!  The seared ahi tuna is da bomb.  We've always had great service.  There are flat screen TVs with sports on all over the place.  Highly recommend.  Great overlook of the city streets while enjoying drinks!

Cute little place upstairs from Sammy T's Music Hall. It's open air, so if you sweat like I do you might not want to hit it in the summer. Food was great, and I think they share a kitchen with Jefferson St. Pub
Late night bar with very neat ambiance
Good schtuff
Food was very good,  the day time bartender was very good and nice as can be
Really comfortable atmosphere. Small, but very open. Food was good and prices were reasonable.
The diablo burger was a surprise. It was cooked to the right temperature with fresh ingredients. I would recommend this place.
Love this place. Food and drinks are very good. Atmosphere is wonderful and the waitress was awesome.
Service is pretty slow and is usually overcrowded.
My favorite bar in Huntsville during the summer.
Pretty dope spot. I just wish it were bigger. Drinks are a bit pricey but to be fair it's the nicest spot on that little strip.

Great service and great views.  The entrance is a little difficult to find (you have to go upstairs).  This place is located right downtown with a grew view of probably the busiest areas of town.  The environment is very open, especially when the weather is nice and the huge windows are open.The staff is friendly, and the drinks are too expensive.  Would go again.

For what it is, it's the best in town. Very cool atmosphere. Great drinks. Best onion rings in town. The brunch is fantastic. Fried goat cheese app comes with an equally fantastic salad. We’ve had nothing here that I can complain about. Good service too. Mr. Taylor has knocked this one out of the park in my opinion. My only complaint would be open an hour earlier on Sunday, we’ll survive though, ha. Thanks for adding this gem to our town!
Best frozen biscuit sandwich within 2 hours of Nashville.
Superb food and drinks. Ask for Saira, she’s amazing. Ask for Ryan if you want good looks.
The Martin is off the chain!!!!!  Love the atmosphere. Fish  tacos are my favorite. Every thing we have tried is super good !
Fish tacos are excellent.

Service and food here is always pretty solid. How can you complain when the weather is beautiful and the balcony windows are raised? The only bad part of this bar is that it's too nice and gets quite crowded late night.
Friendly service. Good food. A little pricey but worth it.
Food was very tasty and the bartender made the best lemon drops I've ever had!!! Will definitely return!
Mac and cheese balls. That is all.
Good atmosphere, great staff.
Great atmosphere,  booze selection,  and a menu that covers any cravings.
Sarah is a great bartender. Had a great time
Great food! Extremely good wings, and flatbread, and cheese curds.
Great modern bar, fast service and cool location
Good food and drinks but a little pricey for the overall quality. Shares a kitchen with JSP selling similar food at 1/3 the cost. 4 stars.
Small friendly bar with good food options
Great staff and wonderful ambiance!

Excellent brunch! Service was great, food was great, the facility is great! I'll be going back! We had biscuits and gravy, chicken and waffles, the eggs Florentino (really just eggs Benny with spinach), and the breakfast platter. All were excellent. Go here so they won't give up on brunch. But only a few of you, because it not bring crowded is great.
I was very disappointed with this place. Their beer selection was underwhelming and their menu was just meh. It was just standard bar food with no twist or anything to make it special.
Great downtown location and place to grab some food or drinks with friends.
Great burger! And my wife liked their sweet heat wings.
Great atmosphere, good beer list.  Would recommend.
Fresh air overlooking downtown. Great service and the history is charming.
A little pricy for the quality of food, but the view's nice.
New bar downtown, great atmosphere, food is overpriced.

Had seared Ahi as an appetizer and fish tacos for meal. Both were amazing. I thought the slaw served with the Ahi was awesome, but my wife didn't care for it due to the horseradish in the dressing. I upgraded to fried green tomatoes as a side and was very glad that I did!
Fun spot! Nice brunch, pleasingly small menu... just enough so you have a choice, not so much that it's overwhelming. If you forget it's above Sammy Ts you don't even feel like you're Huntsville.

Not bad but little hot for me as the place is open to the outdoors. Sort of expensive. Burger looked good wife wanted wings but she always gets them naked so not much taste but that is sort of on her. May go back just when it gets a little cooler. People very nice.
Nice place.  Good food.  Food is a little high but drinks are reasonable.  Open air bar.
good food, service, and prices! a must for a sunday brunch
What an awesome place! Love the view, will definitely be coming back here!
They Dont Do What the other Bars Did on the Strip They Accept All Kinda Money No Matter What color you are The Kinda Jeans you Wear Thats Awesome 👍 For REAL 💯
Nice place for drinks
We didn’t even know this place existed. Our server said it’s only been open one month. We loved it! A cool city vibe, great service, good bar food. Just the kind of thing Huntsville needs!
Very cool atmosphere, especially right when downtown is winding down the work day.  Food was excellent and the staff is top notch.
Make no mistake, this is a bar first and bistro a very distant second. Subpar bar food--burger is a terrible effort along with flatbreads made of frozen, thick dough.

This is the new Huntsville. Such a really cool atmosphere here. The food and service was excellent, as well as the menu selection. I had the grillled cheese toast with tomato soup. Others in our group had the flatbread pizza, chicken wings, chicken sandwich with fries and onion rings. All tasted great. I will be back!
Great food and great service and second level scenary with street view is killer

We checked out The Martin on the Saturday at opening weekend.  We got there as they were opening the doors.  First impression, the steps going upstairs set the tone.  Very old school, green marble,  kind of like stepping into a 1940's hotel.  The open garage doors to outside create a chill environment.  They have unique beer on tap (the Weihenstephan Hefe is normally only found in specialty stores and my fiance was thrilled to see Guinness).  We shared the tuna appetizer, which was great.  Our friend joined us and ate the last piece and ordered another plate!  I also had the shrimp tacos which were wonderful.  The breading was different than normal (almost like hushpuppy breading) and the remoulade sauce was tasty.  We left about 4:30 and they were slammed.  But, it appeared they were able to keep up with the demand.  We were well taken care of.  The prices of some items are steep, but that being said, it's a nice establishment so that is to be expected.  Definitely something different that Huntsville was in need of!
Waited for fifteen minutes at the bar and the bartender never spoke to us to offer us a drink. Cool venue and I hope it improves, but terrible impression for a “grand opening”.

The place is nice but it’s no Sammy T’s.    You probably won’t find dancing Dave at it.  It’s not handicap friendly and has a single person bathroom.  However if you like the typical this is your spot cuz like I said it’s pretty nice.
Awesome! Love it here. Blake and Tippy are amazing.
